Dialogue: 10,0:01:33.49,0:01:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We wish you all a happy new year!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:36.99,0:01:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Have...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.45,0:01:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a good...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.00,0:01:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,year...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.33,0:01:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,everybo...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:42.33,0:01:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,...dy.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:49.67,0:01:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The new year really refreshes your spirit.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:52.30,0:01:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A new start.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:54.09,0:01:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I love things that have "new" in them.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.35,0:01:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a new release, or a new product.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.60,0:02:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Or newlywed, or newcomer! \NThey're bursting with possibilities.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.39,0:02:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}New jackpots and new machines make me \Nwant to go try my luck at pachinko.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.90,0:02:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Sometimes it's hard to see \Nwhat's so "new" about them, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:11.94,0:02:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Like New York or New Orleans for example.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.36,0:02:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Even newspapers aren't really "new" anymore.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.24,0:02:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We should call them "oldspapers". \NThe internet's {\i1}way{\i0} faster and has less bias.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.75,0:02:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,New potatoes! New York pizza!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.37,0:02:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what "newtritious" means?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:26.42,0:02:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The "nu" in "nutritious" has nothing to do with "new".
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.25,0:02:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.18,0:02:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's up, Marii?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.10,0:02:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You know full bloody well what's up!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.76,0:02:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dy"?! Seriously? "Dy"?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.26,0:02:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,D?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.97,0:02:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see a deer?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.68,0:02:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.39,0:02:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about being a delinquent.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.44,0:02:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That junk again?!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:47.27,0:02:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna defeat you!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.82,0:02:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't deny it!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:51.53,0:02:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What about this?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:52.19,0:02:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotion.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:53.24,0:02:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What about this?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.24,0:02:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Depravity.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.11,0:02:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, no, {\i1}no{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.37,0:02:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What, then? What's "D"?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:59.49,0:03:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was my part in our announcement just "dy"?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.54,0:03:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh right, the announcement.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.54,0:03:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that all?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.87,0:03:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Whaddya mean, "is that all"?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.38,0:03:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But you've got to be at the end, Marii.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.05,0:03:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,She's right. The thought of going last makes me tremble...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.26,0:03:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I'd be so nervous, I could see myself saying \N"Have a good year everybo... doo."
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.27,0:03:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How awful...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.48,0:03:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:26.19,0:03:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I'd be mortified if I said something like \N"Have a good year everybo... dow."
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.77,0:03:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How awful...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.78,0:03:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The only one capable of giving that "dy" \Nthe treatment it deserves is you, Marii.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.61,0:03:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:43.24,0:03:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:44.79,0:03:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But isn't a single syllable cutting it a bit short?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.42,0:03:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}What are you talking about? \NLonger doesn't always mean better.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.46,0:03:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I know a certain guy with a short name who works \Na lot harder than a certain guy with a longer name.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.34,0:03:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's very convincing.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.59,0:04:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Jugemu, with the really long name?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.05,0:04:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He never did much besides beat other people's children.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.93,0:04:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Ah! That reminds me, \NI got something for us all from Master.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:08.14,0:04:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They're new year's gifts!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.19,0:04:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone should pick the one they want.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.57,0:04:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The "dip" in "lucky dip" is short for \N"dip-ressingly small amount of money".
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.99,0:04:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.82,0:04:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It might as well be. Japanese people love being humble.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:25.70,0:04:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Well, it's from Master, so we shouldn't \Nget our hopes up too much, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.29,0:04:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he really splashed out this year, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.34,0:04:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For real?!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:33.96,0:04:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, I want this one—
Dialogue: 10,0:04:36.51,0:04:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what was that for?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.05,0:04:38.59,Alt,,0,0,0,,You can go last this time as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.59,0:04:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone knows going first is best!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.30,0:04:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna play rock-paper-scissors to decide?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.22,0:04:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Winner gets to pick first!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.18,0:04:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Rock-paper-scissors!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.23,0:04:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii gets to pick last.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:49.73,0:04:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Gimme another chance!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:51.40,0:04:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's play a different game, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:54.82,0:04:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii goes fifth.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.78,0:04:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii's last.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:57.99,0:05:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Going last is Marii's destiny.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.20,0:05:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The late bird misses the worm.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.12,0:05:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,With that out of the way, shall we choose our gifts?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.74,0:05:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang on a sec!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.74,0:05:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Picking last means I'm at a disadvantage, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.58,0:05:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.17,0:05:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A fat envelope might be stuffed with thousand-yen bills,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.21,0:05:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but a slim one could have one ten thousand-yen bill.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.67,0:05:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Good point.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.05,0:05:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it they say? "There's luck in leftovers"?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.34,0:05:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take it.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.34,0:05:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. I'll start, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.18,0:05:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This thin one... It's gotta be ten thousand yen!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.12,0:05:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:53.62,0:05:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Bzzzt! That's what you get for \Nbeing greedy and rushing.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.25,0:06:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Someone as stingy as our Master \Nwould never give us ten grand!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.17,0:06:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Me next!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.68,0:06:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care about the values, I just want a lot of notes!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.56,0:06:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What a cutie-pie!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.31,0:06:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,She's still just a kid.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.81,0:06:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There {\i1}were{\i0} ten-grand bills!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.27,0:06:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,G-Good for you, Kigu.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.32,0:06:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:20.23,0:06:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Sure, this one.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:24.78,0:06:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I-Is this a two thousand-yen bill?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.62,0:06:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't use these in vending machines...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.62,0:06:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}They don't even have anyone's face on them.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.91,0:06:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}They just seem kinda fake!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.62,0:06:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This throws a spanner in the works.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.71,0:06:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The possibilities are endless now!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.96,0:06:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thin and thick? You guys are so small-minded.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.21,0:06:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget trivial details. Submit to the whims of fate.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.55,0:06:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeny, meeny, miny, mo, catch a tiger by the toe...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.01,0:06:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's not money.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.14,0:06:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a stock certificate.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.68,0:06:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}And it's for {\i1}the{\i0} Central Japan Railway Company! \NOne share's what, six hundred thousand yen?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.52,0:06:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How can one person be so lucky?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.94,0:07:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The last envelope!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.69,0:07:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Over to you, Marii!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.94,0:07:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,On it!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.58,0:07:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a few friggin' coins!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.87,0:07:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That so?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.33,0:07:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You left that one last on purpose!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.04,0:07:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Coins don't equate low value, y'know?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:21.09,0:07:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}There have been commemorative coins \Nworth up to hundreds of thousands of yen.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.51,0:07:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't sound very likely.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.26,0:07:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They're probably foreign coins.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.55,0:07:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Foreign coins?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.93,0:07:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Could be a five hundred won coin.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:34.98,0:07:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How much would that be worth?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.77,0:07:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}At the current exchange rate, \None won equals roughly 0.08 yen.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.31,0:07:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, so about four thousand yen?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.23,0:07:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No, forty yen.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.36,0:07:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That little?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.03,0:07:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Yeah, but you can use five hundred won \Nas a fake five hundred-yen coin if you want to.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.79,0:07:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you can't! That's a crime!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.54,0:07:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,People used to do that all the time.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.96,0:08:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's not limited to won.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.25,0:08:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There could be any coin in that envelope.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.63,0:08:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Or alternatively...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.38,0:08:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be a key!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.34,0:08:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I win!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.59,0:08:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gotta be an apartment key!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.85,0:08:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an impressively greedy leap.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.72,0:08:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}As greedy as a Ginza bar owner \Nduring the economic bubble.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.98,0:08:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,How big d'you reckon it is?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.14,0:08:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Six tatami? Eight? Maybe even ten?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.90,0:08:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think she can measure in anything but tatami.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:23.86,0:08:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the key is for a dungeon.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.40,0:08:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Full of hordes of terrifying monsters!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.20,0:08:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Scary!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.20,0:08:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Awesome! There's bound to be \Na bunch of treasure at the end!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.54,0:08:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.50,0:08:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A chest filled with five hundred won coins!
Dialogue: 9,0:08:43.34,0:08:43.38,Default,,230,191,99,,A chest filled with five hundred won coins!
Dialogue: 9,0:08:43.38,0:08:43.42,Default,,297,123,128,,A chest filled with five hundred won coins!
Dialogue: 9,0:08:43.42,0:08:43.46,Default,,318,102,140,,A chest filled with five hundred won coins!
Dialogue: 9,0:08:43.46,0:08:43.50,Default,,351,69,135,,A chest filled with five hundred won coins!
Dialogue: 9,0:08:43.50,0:08:43.54,Default,,405,15,96,,A chest filled with five hundred won coins!
Dialogue: 9,0:08:43.54,0:08:43.59,Default,,435,-15,32,,A chest filled with five hundred won coins!
Dialogue: 9,0:08:43.59,0:08:43.63,Default,,473,-52,-30,,A chest filled with five hundred won coins!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.25,0:08:43.29,Default,,146,274,-29,,It's not gonna be in won!
Dialogue: 11,0:08:43.29,0:08:43.34,Default,,185,235,24,,It's not gonna be in won!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.34,0:08:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not gonna be in won!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.67,0:08:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, whatever it is, it's probably not a key. Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:49.72,0:08:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A camera?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.38,0:08:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Oh, should we say something \Nto the folks viewing via satellite feed?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.76,0:08:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii should go last.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:56.18,0:08:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Again?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:57.68,0:09:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The last words are the ones people remember most.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.44,0:09:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Really?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.32,0:09:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We wish you all a happy new year!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:07.78,0:09:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Have...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.03,0:09:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a good...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.24,0:09:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,year...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.28,0:09:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,everybo...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.20,0:09:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,...dy.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.46,0:09:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You asshole!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.67,0:09:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii's new year gift is missing!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:32.13,0:09:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.47,0:09:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't good. She's closed off her heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.56,0:09:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't help but wonder what was in the envelope, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.69,0:09:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it really was a key after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:46.69,0:09:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The key to Marii's heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.04,0:10:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That didn't wrap anything up!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:10.84,0:10:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Won.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.89,0:10:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My name is
Dialogue: 10,0:10:21.89,0:10:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Marii.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.60,0:10:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I chased an adorable cat,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.69,0:10:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and ended up lost somehow.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:30.15,0:10:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I remember something I heard a long time ago.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:33.65,0:10:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\q2}A story about a place built from the dreams \Nand wishes of children who never grew up.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.79,0:10:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Could this be Akiha—
Dialogue: 10,0:10:42.04,0:10:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Jizodori shopping street.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:44.46,0:10:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In Sugamo.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:49.59,0:10:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Not Akiba? You mean I dressed as a maid for nothing?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:53.01,0:10:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Maid outfits aren't the Akiba uniform.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.72,0:10:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, a maid!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:57.72,0:10:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A maid?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:59.18,0:11:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Touching them'll take you straight to paradise!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.64,0:11:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They're maid in heaven!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.35,0:11:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's best to touch?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.27,0:11:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The chest area, for sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:08.11,0:11:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where the heart is!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.23,0:11:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Nooo! P-Please, no-no-no...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.12,0:11:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.99,0:11:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Praise be! Thank you!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:23.16,0:11:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are there so many animal-themed clothes?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:27.63,0:11:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}This one with Mt. Fuji looks like \Nit'd bring very good luck indeed!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.25,0:11:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I bet this T-shirt with Kannon \Non it would bring you fortune!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.67,0:11:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Gonna buy it? Y'can't take it with you \Ninto the next world, you know!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:37.55,0:11:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.84,0:11:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The keywords here are "good luck", \N"fortune", and "the next world".
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.68,0:11:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't blend in, things could turn nasty again.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.39,0:11:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we talk about, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.44,0:11:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What about our health?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.32,0:11:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,My shoulders have been so stiff lately.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.65,0:11:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My lower back's killing me.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.78,0:11:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I see pink elephants.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:59.74,0:12:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's alcoholic hallucinosis. {## https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seeing_pink_elephants}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.41,0:12:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Bland conversations like these tire me out.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.95,0:12:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's kick things up a notch.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.83,0:12:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we eat some grilled lamprey?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.75,0:12:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Lampreys are kind of scary.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.79,0:12:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They call them "nine-eyed eels".
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.42,0:12:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They do have a lot of eyes!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.01,0:12:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Those aren't eyes, they're gills.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.80,0:12:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! The soy-boiled carp's looking at me!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:24.06,0:12:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}That reminds me of when my grandma made me \Neat soy-boiled locusts to make my teeth strong.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.48,0:12:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I was made to eat bee larvae.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.02,0:12:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys are minor-league.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.99,0:12:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was made to eat rice made from caddisfly larvae.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.87,0:12:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,When you lift the lid of the rice cooker...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.66,0:12:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,black lumps wiggle and jiggle!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.16,0:12:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.50,0:12:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No more!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.08,0:12:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh look, Kintarou candy.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.67,0:12:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings back memories.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.63,0:12:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It's got the same face running \Nthrough it wherever you cut.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.47,0:13:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What if it had Gankyou's face wherever you cut?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.30,0:13:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What if it had Kukuru's face wherever you cut?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.10,0:13:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't sound like it'd be sweet.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.15,0:13:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's main event:
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.69,0:13:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The shrine of Thornpuller Jizo.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.15,0:13:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}A long time ago, a maidservant \Nswallowed a thorn by mistake,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.61,0:13:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but she was saved by swallowing an image of Jizo.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.32,0:13:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They say you can use the water from here \Nto cure your body's ailments.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.08,0:13:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not Thornpuller Jizo.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.17,0:13:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're thinking of Washing Kannon.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.71,0:13:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.75,0:13:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people make that mistake, apparently.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.59,0:13:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I got tricked somehow.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.80,0:13:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We came all the way here, so if you wanna wash, wash!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.18,0:13:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to cure your eyes, Gan?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.47,0:13:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,More like her attitude, got 'em.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.35,0:13:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would you pour the water for that?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.72,0:13:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,On the heart, I guess.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.93,0:13:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Hey! You wash the statue of Kannon, \Nnot the person themselves!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.19,0:13:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.11,0:13:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I daresay it's rounded Gankyou out a bit.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.86,0:14:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Marii, dear?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.24,0:14:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii... dear?!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:06.91,0:14:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Gan?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.24,0:14:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Bespectacled asshat!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.83,0:14:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Now, now, mind your language, Marii! \NThere's no need to say such things!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.38,0:14:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's rather dangerous, Marii!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.13,0:14:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a beautiful day today. I'm so happy!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:21.47,0:14:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess Thornpuller Jizo's blessing's the real deal!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.43,0:14:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Chest! I'm gonna splash it on my chest!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.52,0:14:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Butt for me!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.81,0:14:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So she {\i1}was{\i0} self-conscious about it...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.35,0:14:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My head!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.56,0:14:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Heart...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.44,0:14:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing really changed.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:40.32,0:14:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.99,0:14:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Why'd only Gankyou benefit?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:47.16,0:14:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't {\i1}actually{\i0} think it did, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.12,0:14:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all so naïve!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.13,0:15:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That was fun and all, but I feel like I rapidly aged now.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.67,0:15:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Forget Girl Power, we've been raising \Nour Granny Power instead.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.72,0:15:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}No worries, eating turtle supposedly \Nmakes your skin all young again.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.10,0:15:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone gets old and wrinkly sooner or later.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.89,0:15:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You get pains in your shoulders, lower back, and knees...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.60,0:15:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Your eyes get cloudy...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.98,0:15:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens to everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.24,0:15:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly got the feeling that whatever will be, will be.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.32,0:15:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's the feeling of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.41,0:15:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Or of losing the strength in your shoulders.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:33.16,0:15:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a pretty mature conversation.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.50,0:15:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I think having conversations like this \Nis how you end up becoming mature.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:44.84,0:15:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My eyes are already cloudy...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:48.18,0:15:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Your glasses steamed up.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.47,0:15:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"I bought this cat 'coz you told me \Nit'd live a thousand years,"
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.15,0:15:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"but it died yesterday!"
Dialogue: 10,0:15:59.94,0:16:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"Oh, dear. Yesterday must have been \Nits thousandth birthday, huh."
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.44,0:16:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your continued appreciation.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.37,0:16:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's April.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.17,0:16:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,April's here.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.13,0:16:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? It's already Ma—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.55,0:16:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Read the room!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:32.14,0:16:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is the 40th of April.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.35,0:16:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.10,0:16:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Kukuru gets the May Blues in May.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.10,0:16:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I can't believe I forgot!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.65,0:16:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure feels like April!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.90,0:16:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're expecting me to get the May Blues again.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:51.20,0:16:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,A-pril! A-pril! A-pril!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.75,0:16:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Kukuru's expression got darker!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:59.79,0:17:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no longer a case of if, but when!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.75,0:17:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything we can do to make her smile?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.34,0:17:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Let's have a staring contest!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.26,0:17:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Daruma, daruma, stare me down.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:12.72,0:17:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Laughs and smiles aren't allowed.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.64,0:17:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A-puh-puh!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.82,0:17:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What about this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:26.28,0:17:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That... hurts...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.24,0:17:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to try harder than that!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.95,0:17:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How's this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.25,0:17:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is dangerous, she's on the verge of an outbreak!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.96,0:17:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there anything else we can try?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.38,0:17:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, we're rakugo performers.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.93,0:17:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't we meant to be pros at making people laugh?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.64,0:17:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! Let's try some rakugo!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.43,0:17:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.14,0:17:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii, you go!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.22,0:18:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather's certainly perked up lately, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.85,0:18:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,May is when you can really start to feel summ—
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.44,0:18:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A-pril! A-pril!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.36,0:18:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I suppose I {\i0}do{\i1} have a resting depression face.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:16.53,0:18:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But it's not like I'm only sad during May.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.37,0:18:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This sucks.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.37,0:18:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They really expect me to get the May Blues.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:25.54,0:18:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She sighed!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.63,0:18:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's started!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.79,0:18:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who gives a damn about May Blues?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.80,0:18:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, she said it.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.09,0:18:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mei and Satsuki are both May children!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:33.76,0:18:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! The May Blues makes you able to see Totoro!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.72,0:18:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How wonderful!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.31,0:18:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They say manga artists hallucinate mythical beasts \Nwhile they're approaching a deadline, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.94,0:18:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,White crocodiles.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.85,0:18:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Green cats.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.98,0:18:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And the assistant who shouldn't exist.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.40,0:18:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamashita.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.61,0:18:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamashita the mythical beast is so scary!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.65,0:18:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope, I've never seen Totoro or Yamashita.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.53,0:18:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Also, I'm not particularly more depressed \Nin May than any other time of year.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.91,0:19:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Not more depressed in May...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.91,0:19:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}You mean you get the June Glooms, \NJuly Slumps, and August Malaise, too?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.00,0:19:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are believable.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:06.04,0:19:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Y'know, these days.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.79,0:19:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they're not real, they should be.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.17,0:19:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, we can't let you suffer alone!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:14.13,0:19:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We should help shoulder the pain!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.09,0:19:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got the June Glooms!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.22,0:19:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.89,0:19:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll all take on a different month.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.35,0:19:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see! I'll go for the November Megrims!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.06,0:19:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,February Woes.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.81,0:19:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,December Depression!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.81,0:19:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Well... we managed to use our \Ngirl power to divide the suffering.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.98,0:19:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But what do my June Glooms involve?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.03,0:19:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Well, it's rainy season, so... \Nmaybe some kind of groin fungus?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.61,0:19:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what one would expect from a cross-dressing boy.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.58,0:19:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:41.33,0:19:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to show your gross lumps to a doctor.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.54,0:19:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any kind of lumps!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.16,0:19:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it's June, wouldn't your attitude turn a bit clammy?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.13,0:19:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A clammy attitude?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.96,0:19:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding onto grudges about things from ages ago.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:55.59,0:19:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Like when they hid your school slippers,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.72,0:20:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or rubbed down the corners of your eraser,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.18,0:20:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,or laughed at your house's screen door,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.14,0:20:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}or wrote the lyrics to that one Alice song \Non the bottom of your desk! {## Refers to "Champion" by Alice}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:05.98,0:20:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never forgive them!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.94,0:20:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You can take the June Glooms.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:12.82,0:20:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}So, since you gave up June, \Nwhich month will you take?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.36,0:20:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, right. Since I'm a woman of extreme kindness,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.20,0:20:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take on the heaviest month of the year.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:24.66,0:20:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one is that?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:27.00,0:20:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The September Blues sound pretty rough.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.29,0:20:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Ah, yeah. Summer's over and you \Ngotta go back to school. It's a drag.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.84,0:20:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}There are kids who get it so bad \Nthey can't even go to school.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:43.18,0:20:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.01,0:20:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh! Don't ask!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.39,0:20:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Then what month am I?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.39,0:20:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I dunno which month to pick.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.48,0:20:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,None of them seem all that heavy.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.23,0:20:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Only you enjoy the entire year that much, Marii.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.40,0:21:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing springs to mind except for May, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.62,0:21:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not like I have the May Blues.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.62,0:21:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, I wonder?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:06.04,0:21:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Energetic people are more susceptible \Nto the May Blues, you know.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:09.08,0:21:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you should watch out, Marii.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:11.29,0:21:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly! I'm fine!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.51,0:21:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya—
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.60,0:21:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamashita!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:26.43,0:21:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,J-Just making sure, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.93,0:21:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamashita isn't standing over there, is he?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.14,0:21:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.98,0:21:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Yamashita?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.44,0:21:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He isn't.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.11,0:21:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I had May Blues all along!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:38.15,0:21:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I would often see Yamashita after that.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.62,0:21:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tormenting me.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.16,0:21:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you just forgive her?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:57.92,0:21:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a little longer.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:01.84,0:22:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,She's pretty tenacious.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:03.97,0:22:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,She's come out of her depression a little at least.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:06.26,0:22:07.47,Alt,,0,0,0,,When...
Dialogue: 10,0:22:07.47,0:22:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When is May gonna end?!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:40.61,0:23:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Buratei Marii here.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:42.73,0:23:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We've all got nail clippers, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:44.36,0:23:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Or nail scissors.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.03,0:23:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you share them with your housemates?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.70,0:23:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't do that with a toothbrush.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:50.74,0:23:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What about earwax picks? Bowls? Cups?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.37,0:23:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Where would you draw the line? \NWhat's in and what's out?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.12,0:24:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I start thinking about it, I can't stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.84,0:24:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, here's the next episode of Rakugo Girls:
Dialogue: 10,0:24:03.25,0:24:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"Life's Butt a Comedy", "The Bear of Ueno", \Nand "Sleep-Talking".
Dialogue: 10,0:24:06.80,0:24:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live His Excellency, Rozen!
